Biggest negative: some higher levels are hair-pullingly finicky, such that it can take more than an hour getting things just #@%& right, tempting you to rage quit. I played on a tablet; I wonder if it's worse on a phone.

From literally the first minutes of gameplay I can tell that this game is amazing and hilarious. The first thing I noticed is how intuitive the controls are, drag from a point to place a bridge or support, click to change between the two, double click to delete and hold to move, I was honestly thinking that the controls would be bad, alright at best, but I can say that for certain that these controls are literally the best they could possibly be. And be next thing I noticed was how when moving a part it puts it above your finger, originally I thought my screen wasn't calibrated but I then realised that, in a game that needs precise placement, this is perfect, it let's you see where the part is exactly and I think that is absolutely genius. Of course, you can't forget the trademark portal humor makes this game absolutely perfect. And for the low low price of 7.99 Australian bucks this game is a steal

Mediocre bridge-building, mediocre attempts at Portal humor, and lazy attempts to cash in on the Portal style.   Interface is awful on a touch screen, where the precision necessary is made fiddly and hidden behind the player's finger. Bridge puzzles are uninspired and don't make clever use of portals, and difficulty progresses like frozen molasses while holding they player's hand along the way. The physics behavior also lacks Portal's intuitive feel, with momentum being very poorly communicated, undermining the fun of portal-based puzzles.

I have never written a review for any game in my life before. However, for this I had to. I'm a huge Half Life and Portal series fan, so having a Portal game in my pocket is amazing! I love the puzzles and the atmosphere. Everything about it makes you feel like you're playing Portal, THEY EVEN GOT GLaDOS IN THIS!  I love this game. So far it's been great!  Except for one thing...the controls. The controls aren't the best. Your thumb gets in the way alot so you have to awkwardly tilt your phone upwards to look under your thumb. Things don't snap as you would expect them to. So it gets very frustrating when you're testing a scenario out only to find out that you didn't connect a line properly.  But apart from the controls, this was a great game, everything else work perfectly. The sound, the puzzles, GLAD0S, the physics, the Portal humor. It's so in depth too!  Thank you so much for this! I recommend that this is a Must buy!
